In article <hoz.6.001291A0@telescan.com> hoz@telescan.com (Rick F. Hoselton) writes:

 > Oops!  You can't be sure that the first block is part of the cycle!

  In many cases you can't, but in this case the mapping is one-to-one
so you can.  (And yes, I have cycle testing programs for RNGs that do
the two-for-one stepping, just to make sure.  But I also keep and
check the first block even in that program, since it saves a lot of
cpu-time when it works.)

